## Field reference

| attribute | constraints |
|---|---|
| `name` | Required. 1-100 characters. Unique. |
| `provider_type` | Required. One of the `provider_type` values below. **Immutable** — changing it forces replacement (the `config` shape is type-coupled). |
| `is_enabled` | Optional boolean. Defaults to `true`. |
| `display_order` | Optional + computed integer `>= 0`. See **`display_order` semantics** below. |
| `config` | Required, **sensitive**. Per-`provider_type` JSON blob set with `jsonencode(...)`; see the per-type tables below. |
| `group_mappings_count` | Read-only. Number of attached group→role mappings. |

### `provider_type` values

| provider_type | meaning |
|---|---|
| `LDAP` | LDAP / Active Directory directory provider. |
| `OIDC` | OpenID Connect provider. |
| `SAML` | SAML 2.0 identity provider. |

## `display_order` semantics

`display_order` controls the login-page ordering of providers:

- **Omit `display_order`** to keep the server's auto-assigned value (`max + 1` on
  create). The value is read back into state (Optional + Computed), so omitting it
  does not produce a perpetual diff.
- **Assign distinct values** for a deterministic login-page order. The backend
  does **not** enforce unique `display_order`; duplicates break ties by `id`.
- **Create cannot set `display_order`** (the server auto-assigns it). When you pin
  a value, the provider applies it with a follow-up PATCH after create; thereafter
  it is set on update. The provider **never** calls the backend's reorder endpoint.

## The `config` JSON blob

`config` is an opaque, per-`provider_type` JSON object written with
`jsonencode(...)`. Its shape is determined by `provider_type` (one table per type
below). Each type carries at least one **secret** field.

**Secret & drift handling.** Every secret field (LDAP `bind_password`, OIDC
`client_secret`, SAML `sp_private_key`) is encrypted at rest and **masked to
`****`** in the API's responses. As with `credential_data`, the provider stores
the **entire `config` from your configuration** and does **not** read it back from
the server — for **all** provider types, not just the secret fields. This is
necessary because the server also **enriches** non-secret defaults (LDAP
`user_search_filter`/`user_attributes`; OIDC `scopes`/`claims_mapping`/
`redirect_uri`; SAML `sp_entity_id`/`sp_acs_url`/`attribute_mapping`), so
reflecting the server value would churn. Consequences:

- After **importing** a provider, `config` is unknown until you re-supply it in
  HCL — secrets cannot be recovered from the masked server value. `config` is
  **excluded from import** (only `id` is set on import).
- Out-of-band changes to the **non-secret** parts of `config` are **not** detected
  as drift, because the whole `config` is preserved from state. This is the
  documented trade-off of the stored-from-config rule (identical to
  `credential_data`).

**License.** `config` create/update (and group-mapping create/update) require an
active license; an unlicensed instance returns a `403` error, surfaced verbatim.
Delete works unlicensed.

### `provider_type = "LDAP"` config

| field | type | required | default | secret |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `server_url` | string (`ldap://` or `ldaps://`) | **yes** | — | no |
| `bind_dn` | string (DN) | **yes** | — | no |
| `bind_password` | string | **yes** | — | **yes** |
| `base_dn` | string (DN) | **yes** | — | no |
| `user_search_filter` | string (must contain `{username}`) | no | `(uid={username})` | no |
| `user_attributes` | object (string→string map, non-empty) | no | `{email = "mail", first_name = "givenName", last_name = "sn"}` | no |
| `group_search_base` | string (DN) or null | no | `null` | no |
| `group_search_filter` | string (parenthesized) | no | `(member={user_dn})` | no |
| `use_tls` | boolean | no | `true` | no |
| `connection_timeout` | integer (1-60) | no | `10` | no |

Example:

```hcl
config = jsonencode({
  server_url    = "ldaps://ldap.example.com:636"
  bind_dn       = "cn=svc,dc=example,dc=com"
  bind_password = var.ldap_bind_password # secret; masked by the API, stored from config
  base_dn       = "ou=people,dc=example,dc=com"
  use_tls       = true
})
```

### `provider_type = "OIDC"` config

| field | type | required | default | secret |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `issuer_url` | string (https; http allowed for local test hosts) | **yes** | — | no |
| `client_id` | string | **yes** | — | no |
| `client_secret` | string | **yes** | — | **yes** |
| `scopes` | array of string (must include `openid`) | no | `["openid", "profile", "email"]` | no |
| `claims_mapping` | object (string→string map) | no | `{email = "email", first_name = "given_name", last_name = "family_name", groups = "groups"}` | no |
| `redirect_uri` | string (http/https) or null | no | auto-generated | no |
| `additional_params` | object (string→string map) | no | `{}` | no |

Example:

```hcl
config = jsonencode({
  issuer_url    = "https://login.example.com"
  client_id     = "mistershell"
  client_secret = var.oidc_client_secret # secret; masked by the API, stored from config
  scopes        = ["openid", "profile", "email"]
})
```

### `provider_type = "SAML"` config

| field | type | required | default | secret |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `idp_entity_id` | string | **yes** | — | no |
| `idp_sso_url` | string (https; http allowed for local test hosts) | **yes** | — | no |
| `idp_x509_cert` | string (PEM certificate) | **yes** | — | no |
| `sp_entity_id` | string or null | no | auto-generated | no |
| `sp_acs_url` | string (http/https) or null | no | auto-generated | no |
| `attribute_mapping` | object (string→string map) | no | `{email = "urn:oid:0.9.2342.19200300.100.1.3", first_name = "urn:oid:2.5.4.42", last_name = "urn:oid:2.5.4.4", groups = "memberOf"}` | no |
| `sign_requests` | boolean | no | `false` | no |
| `want_assertions_signed` | boolean | no | `true` | no |
| `sp_private_key` | string (PEM key) or null | no | `null` | **yes** |
| `sp_x509_cert` | string (PEM certificate) or null | no | `null` | no |

Example:

```hcl
config = jsonencode({
  idp_entity_id  = "https://idp.example.com/metadata"
  idp_sso_url    = "https://idp.example.com/sso"
  idp_x509_cert  = file("idp.crt")
  sp_private_key = var.saml_sp_private_key # secret; masked by the API, stored from config
})
```

